item.title: New RS3server Development Team
item.dc:creator: @Tutorial Tutorial
item.description:
@Tutorial wrote:

I’m not going to create an application simply because of the ideas you have for your server, but I would like to help you make your application format better:

Coding Experience: This is okay. What other server have you worked with: This doesn't come close to mattering when you are working with one standard form of language. Email Address: This is okay. Do you know how to make a webclient through jarring/signing: This is okay, but is probably one of the most simplest things anyone could learn. Which would you consider your best 317/508/600+: Once again, this is something that doesn't matter. Revision does not change the language you use. On a scale of 1/10 what you say your at for coding: This is pretty much just a re-worded form of the first part of the application format.

Anyways, good luck on your project.

Read full topic
